      • getAll

        public java.util.List<SensorDataEntity> getAll​(java.lang.String sensorIp)
        Fetch all entries of sensor data for the input sensor IP. The results are be ordered by automatically generated ID of sensor data entries. Return an empty list if the input sensorIp doesn't exist in the database or there is no data entry for the input sensor IP.
        Parameters:
        sensorIp - The IPv6 address of the sensor from which the data you want to fetch generated.
        Returns:
        A list of SensorDataEntity.

      • getAllLaterThan

        public java.util.List<SensorDataEntity> getAllLaterThan​(java.util.Date timeStamp)
        Get all entries of sensor data that were created later than the input timeStamp. The results are ordered by sensor data ID. Throw NullPointerException if the input timeStamp is null;
        Parameters:
        timeStamp - The time stamp you want to query
        Returns:
        A list of SensorDataEntity

      • getAllLaterThan

        public java.util.List<SensorDataEntity> getAllLaterThan​(java.lang.String sensorIp,
                                                        java.util.Date timeStamp)
        Get all entries of sensor data that were created later than the input timeStamp for the input sensor IP. The results are ordered by sensor data ID. Return an empty list if the input sensorIp doesn't exist. Throws NullPointerException if the input timeStamp is null;
        Parameters:
        timeStamp - The time stamp you want to query.
        Returns:
        A list of SensorDataEntity
